HEADWORD: Sherif
<hw>Sher"if</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ar. <ets>sher⟦imac⟧f</ets>
noble, holy, n., a prince.]</ety> <def>A member of an Arab princely
family descended from Mohammed through his son-in-law Ali and daughter
Fatima. The Grand Shereef is the governor of Mecca.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

